Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. records.addlTxt: 12:58 PM Defendant Jacob A Ruetten appeared by video, in custody from JCJ.  Attorney Emily Hynek in court for State of Wisconsin. SPD Attorney Sebion appeared specially to provide information to the court. Atty has been located, attorney found is not available for tomorrow's preliminary hearing. Defendant now wants to seek help from an attorney.  No threats or promises to waive time limits. Reschedule the preliminary hearing.
Preliminary hearing on October 28, 2022 at 09:30 am.

4:03 PM Defendant Jacob A Ruetten appeared by video, in custody from JCJ. Attorney Emily Hynek in court for State of Wisconsin. Attorney Carly Sebion appears via zoom.  Defendant still intending to represent himself at this time. Defendant will not be receiving any counsel before Dec 30 continuing in pro se status.  Atty Sebion responds. States question - who do they communicate with? Atty Sebion - for now defendant proceeding pro se. At this point and time, Defendant states he is representing himself. Court reiterates past finding, defendant demonstrated he understand concepts of representing himself. Court deems him to be representing himself. Appropriate for DA's office to communicate the defendant, knowing at any point in time he can request counsel. Cautioned of potential consequences. State informs if defendant wants to communicate, he can contact jail staff. Schedule preliminary hearing, 10/28 @ 9:30 allowing 30 minutes. Court confirmed with defendant, he is willing to waive time limits.
Status hearing on October 3, 2022 at 04:00 pm.
Pre-trial conference on September 7, 2022 at 10:00 am.
Court questioned defendant on his understanding of the waiver.  Defendant stated he understood.  Court found that the defendant knowingly and intelligently waived his right to attorney.

1:11 PM Defendant Jacob A Ruetten appeared by video, in custody of JCJ.  Attorney Crystal Jensen in court for State of Wisconsin. Court advised the defendant of the charges and possible penalties contained in the complaint.  He understood. Court explained his attorney rights. He wishes to waive counsel. Waive reading of the complaint.  PTC 9/7, then will address preliminary hearing issue.

9:10 AM Defendant Jacob A Ruetten appeared by video, in custody.  Attorney Emily Hynek in court for State of Wisconsin. Attorney Carly Sebion appears specially for defendant. Trying to move forward Pro Se. Atty Sebion makes statement. Needs to fill out a RTAW form and recall his case at 1:00PM.

Adjourned initial appearance on August 29, 2022 at 09:00 am.
